keyPoints:
instanceof: runtime type check — returns boolean
Classic: if (a instanceof Dog) { Dog d = (Dog) a; d.bark(); }
Pattern matching (Java 16+): if (a instanceof Dog d) { d.bark(); }
Null check: null instanceof Anything → false (safe, no NPE)
Excessive instanceof = code smell — prefer polymorphism
Sealed classes (Java 17+) + pattern matching in switch = exhaustive dispatch

